      "writtenOn": "2018-10-12T15:32:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The infra task driver (in an upcoming CL, but also was present in the initial experiment: https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/156233/44/infra/bots/task_drivers/infra_tests/infra_tests.go#100) has a step whose purpose is just to set the environment for its sub-steps.  I guess we could give it a name like \"set environment\" but it\u0027s more typing for little to no benefit.  Once we get to the point where we\u0027re displaying steps in a UI we may find that anonymous steps are hard to represent.  At that point we can make names mandatory if necessary.",
      "parentUuid": "4352ef04_9235be62",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 87,
        "endChar": 66
